    {
      "id": "time",
      "icon": "🕐",
      "title": "Telling time",
      "subtitle": "Il-Ħin — what time is it?",
      "intro": "Maltese has no word for 'o'clock' — you just say the number. Note: 1 and 2 use special forms (is-siegħa, is-sagħtejn). For everything else, the cardinal number with the article.",
      "facts": [
        "Filgħodu = AM (morning, until noon).",
        "Wara nofsinhar = PM (afternoon, after 12 noon).",
        "Filgħaxija = evening (roughly 6pm to 10pm).",
        "Ta' billejl = night (after 10pm).",
        "There's no Maltese word for 'o'clock' — just the number with its article."
      ],
      "hours": [
        {"n": 1, "mt": "is-siegħa", "en": "1 o'clock"},
        {"n": 2, "mt": "is-sagħtejn", "en": "2 o'clock"},
        {"n": 3, "mt": "it-tlieta", "en": "3 o'clock"},
        {"n": 4, "mt": "l-erbgħa", "en": "4 o'clock"},
        {"n": 5, "mt": "il-ħamsa", "en": "5 o'clock"},
        {"n": 6, "mt": "is-sitta", "en": "6 o'clock"},
        {"n": 7, "mt": "is-sebgħa", "en": "7 o'clock"},
        {"n": 8, "mt": "it-tmienja", "en": "8 o'clock"},
        {"n": 9, "mt": "id-disgħa", "en": "9 o'clock"},
        {"n": 10, "mt": "l-għaxra", "en": "10 o'clock"},
        {"n": 11, "mt": "il-ħdax", "en": "11 o'clock"},
        {"n": 12, "mt": "nofsinhar", "en": "12 noon"},
        {"n": 0, "mt": "nofsillejl", "en": "midnight"}
      ],
      "patterns": [
